                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>
                                <height min="4" max="5" unit="cm">4-5</height>
                                <note type="palaeographic" xml:lang="en">
                                    <p>Dextrograde direction, horizontal alignment, vertical module, irregular <term xml:lang="la">ductus</term>, triangular interpunction, centered layout.</p>
                                    
                                    <p><g type="pl">D</g> wide, with square module;</p>
                                    
                                    <p><g type="pl">M</g> composed of four oblique strokes;</p>
                                    
                                    <p><g type="pl">N</g> with vertical lateral strokes.</p>
                                </note>
                                <note type="palaeographic" xml:lang="it">
                                    <p>Verso destrorso, andamento orizzontale, modulo verticale, <term xml:lang="la">ductus</term> irregolare, interpunzione triangoliforme, impaginazione centrata.</p>
                                    
                                    <p><g type="pl">D</g> ampia, dal modulo quadrato;</p>
                                    
                                    <p><g type="pl">M</g> composta da quattro aste oblique;</p>
                                    
                                    <p><g type="pl">N</g> con le aste laterali verticali.</p>
                                </note>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote xml:lang="en">
                                <p>The inscribed field is framed by a molded border, the lower side of which is now lost.</p>
                                
                                <p>The figurative decoration of the sarcophagus, now lost, was described by <bibl ref="#bertolini1874a">Bertolini</bibl>: the tomb bore on both pediments of the lid the monogram of Constantine. The sides of the inscription had sculpted on the front, one a male head, the other a female head; on the sides of the inscription there were two arches supported by columns and in the center a small patera. On the minor faces there was on the north side an arch of equal workmanship and beneath it two vases, and on the south side the arch without other figures.</p>
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:lang="it">
                                <p>Lo specchio epigrafico è delimitato da una cornice modanata, il cui lato inferiore è oggi perduto.</p>
                                
                                <p>The figurative decoration of the sarcophagus, now lost, was described by <bibl ref="#bertolini1874a">Bertolini</bibl> as follows: "this tomb bears on both pediments of the lid the monogram of Constantine. The sides of the inscription have sculpted on the front, one a male head, the other a female head; on the sides of the inscription there are two arches supported by columns and in the center a small patera. On the minor faces there is on the north side an arch of equal workmanship and beneath it two vases, and on the south side the arch without other figures".</p>
                            </decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
